<subSubSection id="C37A1F941351FFBD0841FB2AFC78FB06" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDF4C1F1351FFBD0841FB2AFC78FB06" blockId="2.[264,1325,1188,1814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B914900D1351FFBD0841FB2AFE0BFB5E" bold="true" box="[312,456,1188,1214]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Etymology:</emphasis>
The epithet of new species from 
<emphasis id="B914900D1351FFBD0A18FB2BFC79FB5E" box="[865,954,1189,1214]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">pulcher</emphasis>
(L., meaning beautiful), referring to the distinct and beautiful color pattern of the wings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37A1F941351FFBD0841FB7AFD79F996" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="materials_examined">
